      <h2>What to Look For: Used Excavator Inspection</h2>

      <h3>1. Undercarriage Condition</h3>

      <p><strong>Check These Components:</strong>
      <br>• Track pads: Wear limit? Replacement cost RM15,000-RM25,000
      <br>• Rollers and idlers: Play? Noise? Leaks?
      <br>• Sprockets: Wear pattern? Tooth condition?
      <br>• Track tension: Proper adjustment?
      <br><strong>Rule of Thumb:</strong> Undercarriage should have 40%+ life remaining. If tracks need replacement soon, negotiate price reduction.</p>

      <h3>2. Engine Performance</h3>

      <p><strong>Check These Items:</strong>
      <br>• Cold start: Difficult? Excessive smoke?
      <br>• Idle: Smooth? Missing? Rough?
      <br>• Full power: Acceleration responsive?
      <br>• Oil pressure: Within spec?
      <br>• Coolant: Clean? No oil mixing?
      <br>• Exhaust: Excessive black smoke? (burning oil)
      <br><strong>Test Drive:</strong> Operate for 30 minutes. Monitor temperature, power, unusual sounds.</p>

      <h3>3. Hydraulic System</h3>

      <p><strong>Check These Points:</strong>
      <br>• Cylinders: Leaks? Rod pitting?
      <br>• Hoses: Cracks? Bulges? Leaks?
      <br>• Pump noise: Whining? Cavitation?
      <br>• Functions: All smooth? Slow? Jerky?
      <br><strong>Function Test:</strong> Cycle all functions (boom, stick, bucket, swing, travel). Any hesitation or weakness indicates hydraulic issues.</p>

      <h3>4. Cabin & Electronics</h3>

      <p><strong>Check These Features:</strong>
      <br>• Dashboard: All gauges working?
      <br>• A/C: Cooling properly? (RM3,000-RM5,000 to fix)
      <br>• Joysticks: Smooth? Loose?
      <br>• Seat: Condition? Adjustments working?
      <br>• Safety systems: Emergency stop? Lockout?</p>

      <h3>5. Service History</h3>

      <p><strong>Ask For Documentation:</strong>
      <br>• Service records: Regular maintenance?
      <br>• Oil analysis: Any issues detected?
      <br>• Major repairs: What was replaced?
      <br>• Hour meter: Actual hours verified?
      <br><strong>Red Flags:</strong> Missing service history, inconsistent hour readings, signs of major repairs not documented.</p>

      <h2>Used Excavator Age: What's Optimal?</h2>

      <h3>1-3 Years Old: Sweet Spot</h3>

